e="text/javascript">vl['t1_2xu2'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2xu2')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2xu2" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Here's some evidence from Stevenson &amp; Wolfers that happiness/life satisfaction is proportional to the log of income: <a href="http://freakonomics.blogs.nytimes.com/2008/04/22/the-economics-of-happiness-part-4-are-rich-people-happier-than-poor-people/" rel="nofollow">blog post</a>, <a href="http://bpp.wharton.upenn.edu/betseys/papers/Happiness.pdf" rel="nofollow">pdf article</a>.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2xu2"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2xu2" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2xu2')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2xu2" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2xu2')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2xu2" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/30k/rationality_quotes_november_2010/2xu2?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2xu2" href="#2xme" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2xu2" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2xu2')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2xu2 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2xu2" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2xo3" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2xo3" class="parent"><a name="2xo3" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2xo3" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2xo3" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2xo3" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/NihilCredo/">NihilCredo</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">10 November 2010 08:32:51PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2xo3'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2xo3')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2xo3" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2xo3" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/NihilCredo/">NihilCredo</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">10 November 2010 08:32:51PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2xo3'>4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2xo3'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2xo3')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2xo3" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>With some constraints, of course.</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>"Here, have a penny."</p>
  
  <p>"You bastard!"</p>
</blockquote></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2xo3"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2xo3" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2xo3')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2xo3" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2xo3')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2xo3" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/30k/rationality_quotes_november_2010/2xo3?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2xo3" href="#2xme" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2xo3" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2xo3')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2xo3 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2xo3" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2xp8" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2xp8" class="parent"><a name="2xp8" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2xp8" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2xp8" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2xp8" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Psy-Kosh/">Psy-Kosh</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">10 November 2010 11:40:05PM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2xp8'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2xp8')">[+] (6 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2xp8" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2xp8" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Psy-Kosh/">Psy-Kosh</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">10 November 2010 11:40:05PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2xp8'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2xp8'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2xp8')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2xp8" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>How does ln(dollars) approximate utilions? It's obvious that utilions are generally not fully linear in dollars, and they're certainly not equivalent, but how does the log of dollars, specifically, approximate utility?</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2xp8"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2xp8" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2xp8')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2xp8" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2xp8')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2xp8" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/30k/rationality_quotes_november_2010/2xp8?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2xp8" href="#2xme" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2xp8" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2xp8')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2xp8 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2xp8" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_2xp8" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_2xp8" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2xr8" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2xr8" class="parent"><a name="2xr8" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2xr8" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2xr8" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2xr8" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/shokwave/">shokwave</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">11 November 2010 06:18:11AM</span><span class="votes " >0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2xr8'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2xr8')">[+] (5 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2xr8" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2xr8" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/shokwave/">shokwave</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">11 November 2010 06:18:11AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2xr8'>0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2xr8'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2xr8')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2xr8" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>If there is some mathematical reason why, I would love to know. I was going off the observation that the natural logarithm approximates the kind of diminishing returns that economists generally agree applies to the utility of wealth. This means that, very roughly, the logarithm of dollars is the 'revealed preference' utility.</p>

<p>It was actually more of a joke about that assumption, because it suggests that a 50 dollar meal is preferred four times as much to a 3 dollar candy bar - a bit odd, but perfectly natural if you like candy bars.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2xr8"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2xr8" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2xr8')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2xr8" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2xr8')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2xr8" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/30k/rationality_quotes_november_2010/2xr8?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2xr8" href="#2xp8" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2xr8" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2xr8')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2xr8 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2xr8" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_2xr8" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_2xr8" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2xr9" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2xr9" class="parent"><a name="2xr9" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2xr9" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2xr9" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2xr9" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/JoshuaZ/">JoshuaZ</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">11 November 2010 06:26:09AM</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2xr9'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2xr9')">[+] (3 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2xr9" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2xr9" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/JoshuaZ/">JoshuaZ</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">11 November 2010 06:26:09AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2xr9'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2xr9'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2xr9')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2xr9" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Well, log does that. But show does square root also. Lots of functions have diminishing marginal returns.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2xr9"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2xr9" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2xr9')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2xr9" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2xr9')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2xr9" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/30k/rationality_quotes_november_2010/2xr9?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2xr9" href="#2xr8" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2xr9" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2xr9')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2xr9 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2xr9" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_2xr9" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_2xr9" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2xrg" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2xrg" class="parent"><a name="2xrg" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2xrg" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2xrg" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2xrg" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/b1shop/">b1shop</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">11 November 2010 06:48:38AM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2xrg'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2xrg')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2xrg" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2xrg" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/b1shop/">b1shop</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">11 November 2010 06:48:38AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2xrg'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2xrg'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2xrg')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2xrg" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I can think of two good reasons to model diminishing returns with the natural log.</p>

<p>Logs produce nice units in the regression coefficients. A log-lin function (that is -- log'd dependent, linear independent) says that a percent increase in X results in a &lt;coefficient&gt; unit increase in Y. Similar statements are true for lin-log and log-log, the latter of which produces elasticities.</p>

<p>y=ln(x) and y=sqrt(x) will both fit data in a similar manner, so it makes sense to go with the one that makes for easy interpretation.</p>

<p>Additionally, the natural log frequently shows up in financial economics, most prominently in continuous interest but also notably in returns, which seem to follow the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Log-normal_distribution" rel="nofollow">log-normal distribution</a>.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2xrg"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2xrg" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2xrg')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2xrg" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2xrg')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2xrg" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/30k/rationality_quotes_november_2010/2xrg?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2xrg" href="#2xr9" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2xrg" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2xrg')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2xrg class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2xrg" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_2xrg" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_2xrg" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2xrk" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2xrk" class="parent"><a name="2xrk" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2xrk" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2xrk" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2xrk" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Manfred/">Manfred</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">11 November 2010 06:55:14AM</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2xrk'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2xrk')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2xrk" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2xrk" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Manfred/">Manfred</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">11 November 2010 06:55:14AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2xrk'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2xrk'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2xrk')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2xrk" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Of course, there's the problem with pathological behavior near 0.</p>

<p>Or the utility of money could quite reasonably be bounded.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2xrk"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2xrk" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2xrk')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2xrk" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2xrk')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2xrk" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/30k/rationality_quotes_november_2010/2xrk?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2xrk" href="#2xrg" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2xrk" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2xrk')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2xrk class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2xrk" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2xre" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2xre" class="parent"><a name="2xre" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2xre" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2xre" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2xre" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/shokwave/">shokwave</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">11 November 2010 06:40:48AM</span><span class="votes " >0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2xre'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2xre')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2xre" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2xre" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/shokwave/">shokwave</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">11 November 2010 06:40:48AM</span><spa