n><span class="comment-date">09 November 2010 05:12:21AM</span><span class="votes " >0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2xd4'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2xd4')">[+] (83 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2xd4" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2xd4" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Perplexed/">Perplexed</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">09 November 2010 05:12:21AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2xd4'>0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2xd4'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2xd4')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2xd4" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Upvoted, but even with communication beforehand, the rational move in a one-shot PD is to defect.  Unless there is some way to make binding commitments, or unless there is some kind of weird acausal influence connecting the players.  Regardless of whether the other player is human and rational, or silicon and dumb as a rock.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2xd4"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2xd4" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2xd4')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2xd4" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2xd4')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2xd4" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/30k/rationality_quotes_november_2010/2xd4?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2xd4" href="#2xck" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2xd4" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2xd4')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2xd4 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2xd4" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_2xd4" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_2xd4" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2y7k" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2y7k" class="parent"><a name="2y7k" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2y7k" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2y7k" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2y7k" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Vladimir_Nesov/">Vladimir_Nesov</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">14 November 2010 10:51:52AM</span><span class="votes " >0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2y7k'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2y7k')">[+] (7 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2y7k" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2y7k" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Vladimir_Nesov/">Vladimir_Nesov</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">14 November 2010 10:51:52AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2y7k'>0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2y7k'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2y7k')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2y7k" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>Upvoted, but even with communication beforehand, the rational move in a one-shot PD is to defect.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Taboo "rational".</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>Unless there is some way to make binding commitments, or unless there is some kind of weird acausal influence connecting the players.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Acausal control is not something <em>additional</em>, it's structure that already exists in a system if you know where to look for it. And typically, it's everywhere, to <em>some</em> extent.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2y7k"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2y7k" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2y7k')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2y7k" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2y7k')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2y7k" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/30k/rationality_quotes_november_2010/2y7k?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2y7k" href="#2xd4" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2y7k" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2y7k')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2y7k class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2y7k" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_2y7k" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_2y7k" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2y80" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2y80" class="parent"><a name="2y80" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2y80" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2y80" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2y80" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/shokwave/">shokwave</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">14 November 2010 01:07:36PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2y80'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2y80')">[+] (6 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2y80" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2y80" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/shokwave/">shokwave</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">14 November 2010 01:07:36PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2y80'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2y80'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2y80')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2y80" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>Taboo "rational".</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Highest-scoring move, adjective applied to the course that maximises fulfillment of desires.</p>

<p>The best move in a one-shot PD is to defect against a cooperator.</p>

<p>With no communication or precommitment, and with the knowledge that it is a one-shot PD, the overwhelming outcome is both defect. Adding communication to the mix creates a non-zero chance you can convince your opponent to cooperate - which <em>increases</em> the utility of defecting.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2y80"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2y80" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2y80')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2y80" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2y80')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2y80" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/30k/rationality_quotes_november_2010/2y80?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2y80" href="#2y7k" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2y80" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2y80')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2y80 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2y80" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_2y80" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_2y80" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2y83" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2y83" class="parent"><a name="2y83" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2y83" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2y83" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2y83" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Vladimir_Nesov/">Vladimir_Nesov</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">14 November 2010 02:03:41PM</span><span class="votes " >0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2y83'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2y83')">[+] (5 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2y83" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2y83" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Vladimir_Nesov/">Vladimir_Nesov</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">14 November 2010 02:03:41PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2y83'>0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2y83'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2y83')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2y83" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>Adding communication to the mix creates a non-zero chance you can convince your opponent to cooperate - which increases the utility of defecting.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>There is a question of what will actually happen, but also more relevant questions of what will happen if you do X, for various values of X. If you convince the opponent to cooperate, it's one thing, not related to the case of convincing your opponent to cooperate <em>if you cooperate</em>.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2y83"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2y83" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2y83')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2y83" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2y83')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2y83" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/30k/rationality_quotes_november_2010/2y83?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2y83" href="#2y80" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2y83" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2y83')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2y83 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2y83" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_2y83" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_2y83" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2y8e" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2y8e" class="parent"><a name="2y8e" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2y8e" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2y8e" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2y8e" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/shokwave/">shokwave</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">14 November 2010 02:48:57PM</span><span class="votes " >0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2y8e'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2y8e')">[+] (4 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2y8e" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2y8e" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/shokwave/">shokwave</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">14 November 2010 02:48:57PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2y8e'>0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2y8e'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2y8e')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2y8e" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
