ment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2wlw" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/James_K/">James_K</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 November 2010 03:39:03AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2wlw'>4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2wlw'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2wlw')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2wlw" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>In circumstances like that I find I have to laugh, if only to keep from weeping.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2wlw"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2wlw" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2wlw')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2wlw" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2wlw')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2wlw" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/30k/rationality_quotes_november_2010/2wlw?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2wlw" href="#2wke" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2wlw" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2wlw')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2wlw class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2wlw" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2xp2" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2xp2" class="parent"><a name="2xp2" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2xp2" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2xp2" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2xp2" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/PhilGoetz/">PhilGoetz</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">10 November 2010 11:28:01PM</span><span class="votes " >0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2xp2'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2xp2')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2xp2" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2xp2" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/PhilGoetz/">PhilGoetz</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">10 November 2010 11:28:01PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2xp2'>0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2xp2'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2xp2')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2xp2" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>He could have also been thinking about the Declaration of Independence, the Declaration of the Rights of Man, and various other documents.  (I'd list the Magna Carta, but it didn't really have the effect it's credited with.  It was a few lines in a larger document that was more concerned with the hunting privileges of nobles than with the rights of man, and that was nullified before the year was out.)</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2xp2"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2xp2" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2xp2')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2xp2" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2xp2')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2xp2" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/30k/rationality_quotes_november_2010/2xp2?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2xp2" href="#2wj6" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2x