<p>I would still say that torture was used to break his will. To say this would be accurate, if not precise (because I'm not specifying whether I mean a particular act or an institutionalized practice).  Whether his will proved too easy to break to satisfy the electorate is another matter.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2wgv"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2wgv" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2wgv')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2wgv" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2wgv')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2wgv" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/30k/rationality_quotes_november_2010/2wgv?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2wgv" href="#2wgq" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2wgv" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2wgv')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2wgv class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2wgv" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2wc2" class="morechildren" ><div id="pre_t1_2wc2" class="parent"></div><div id="entry_t1_2wc2" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2wc2" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'></div><div id="display_t1_2wc2" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"></div><div id="body_t1_2wc2" class="comment-content"><span class="morecomments"><a style="font-size: smaller; font-weight: bold" id="more_t1_2wc2" href="javascript:void()" onclick="return morechildren(this, 't3_30k', ['2wc2'], 3)">load more comments<span