<p>I figure this particular one strikes some as a bit iffy since the metaphor is so close to the salient metaphor the actual creationists are using and treating as a non-metaphor. Metaphors, like "God wrote life", closely associated with unsympathetic real-world groups tend to carry a bit extra baggage. The matter is of course confused further by the original context where this was written as a response to creationists.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2wch"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2wch" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2wch')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2wch" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2wch')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2wch" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/30k/rationality_quotes_november_2010/2wch?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2wch" href="#2wc6" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2wch" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2wch')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2wch class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2wch" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2whm" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2whm" class="parent"><a name="2whm" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2whm" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2whm" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2whm" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Tiiba/">Tiiba</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 November 2010 08:18:47PM</span><span class="votes " >0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2whm'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2whm')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2whm" class="" ><d