"><a name="2wp9" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2wp9" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2wp9" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2wp9" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Larks/">Larks</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 November 2010 02:53:05PM</span><span class="votes " >4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2wp9'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2wp9')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2wp9" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2wp9" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Larks/">Larks</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 November 2010 02:53:05PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2wp9'>4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2wp9'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2wp9')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2wp9" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>He only has to deny that it exists.</p>

<p>Alternatively, he could lock himself onto a sun-destroying path, and then forcibly do an unBayesian update away from the existence of the sun.</p>

